page.title: 05Bird Walk
page.content: When I came home from school I picked up my binoculars and went outside.I looked for any birds in the garden and there was a thrush sitting on the grass.The thrush was trying to peck a worm out of the ground and it succeeded.I went on to the shore at Rubhmor to look for some seabirds.As I came round the corner I saw two swans with their seven cygnets.The little cygnets were all fluffy and brown.I came off the shore at the big house and went up to the workshop where I went up the bank and into the forest.In the middle of the forest I saw a little treecreeper climbing up the side of a tree.I could not miss it because of its white breast and its brown back.I still did not see the golden eagle that is supposed to be in the forest.
